		if-statement

Use if to specify a block of code to be executed, if a specified condition is true.

Use else to specify a block of code to be executed, if the same condition is false.

Use else if to specify a new condition to test, if the first conditon is false.

Use switch to specify many alternative blocks of code to be executed.

Code Refactoring

Is the process of restructuring existing computer code.
Changing the following without changing its external behaviour.

Refactoring improves non-Function attributes of the software.

Advantages include improved code readability and reduced complixity.

These can improve source-code maintainability.

 



